        </div>
        <p><strong>Workflow insight:</strong> nmap → searchsploit every version → prioritize unauthenticated services → read exploit → run exploit → root. Don't get stuck manually poking services when searchsploit can skip you ahead.</p>
        <p><strong>Persistence note:</strong> inetd-based shells are not persistent. The port closes after your session ends or machine restarts. Re-run the exploit to reconnect.</p>
